Last Revised:
February 27, 2024
Sphero, Inc. (“
Sphero
”, "
we
" or “
us
”) is committed to protecting your and, where applicable, your child’s privacy.
This
Privacy Policy
describes how your and, where applicable, your child’s data is collected, used, and disclosed by Sphero from the mobile application known as the
Sphero Play App
(the “
Application
”), for the toys controlled by the Application (the “
Toy(s)
”). This Policy does not apply to websites, applications, or services that display or link to different privacy policies. Any third parties described below that process your data may not adhere to this Privacy Policy; Sphero expressly disclaims any and all liability for unauthorized processing by such third parties. For subjects not covered in this Policy, the
Main Sphero Privacy Policy
controls.
1.
Data We Collect.
We collect Contact Data, Sensor Data, Mobile Data (together with Contact Data and Sensor Data, “
Personal Data
”), and Toy Data, each as defined below
a.
Data You Provide to Us Upon Toy Configuration.
•
Sensor Data:
You may choose to use certain features of the Application that require access to the microphone or location data of your device.
b.
Data Collected Automatically via Technology on our Services.
The examples of Data given below are illustrative and subject to change in Sphero’s sole discretion.
•
Mobile Data.
If you download our Application, we may collect the type of mobile device and its software version.
•
Toy Data.
Using Bluetooth, the Toy may transmit Toy Data to the Application such as Toy identifier, when a Toy connects to an Application, date/time stamps, non-personal diagnostic data regarding how you use the Application, MAC Address or device identifier depending on the Toy, accelerometer data, crashes, and the like.
2.
Use of Your Data.
Subject to your Rights and Choices below, we use your Data as follows.
a.
Contact Data.
We use your Contact Data to provide support services if you contact us. For example:
• If you contact us through customer service or support, we will use your Contact Data to respond to your comments and questions, and to provide customer service.
b.
Sensor Data.
We process this data on your device, not as part of an information society service. We will obtain consent in the Application before collecting this data, and you may cease collection of this data at any time by consulting your Application’s settings. However, some features of the Application or Toy may not function without the Sensor Data. We process this data to personalize your experience and to provide features in the Application. For example:
• We use Sensor Data from your microphone to enable the Scream Drive feature.
• We use Sensor Data from your location on Android Devices to enable Bluetooth functionality.
c.
Mobile Data and Toy Data.
We use the Toy Data and Mobile Data for our legitimate business interests in the improvement of our Application and Toys, and the creation of a personalized user experience, including in the following ways:
• to understand a user’s engagement in an activity or feature, for example which activities on the Toy the user played, time spent on pages, and data about any crashes during use, to Sphero’s servers, which may be hosted by a Service Company.
• to operate and improve our Application and Services, internal operations, and systems, along with the Service Companies;
• to improve the quality of experience when you interact with our Application and Services;
• understand you and your preferences to enhance your experience and enjoyment using our Services;
• to derive information about the demographics that use our Services; and
• to protect, investigate, and deter against fraudulent, unauthorized, or illegal activity.
The legitimate interests we rely on for this processing are:
• to create, provide, support, and maintain innovative Toys, Applications, and features that enable people, including children, to enjoy Toys and Applications that promote their well-being; and
• to secure our platform and network and investigate suspicious activity or violations of our terms or policies.
d.
Support
. If you contact us for support through the Application, we may collect first and last name, email address, and any information you choose to include in your query.
3.
Service Companies.
We use third-party
Service Companies
to help provide and host the Application and the Service, to help with direct marketing, to help us automatically collect the Mobile and Toy data, to analyze the Toy Data, and to further our other legitimate business interests. We provide Personal Data to our Service Companies or other trusted businesses or persons to process it for us, based on our instructions and in compliance with this Privacy Policy and any other appropriate confidentiality and security measures. If Sphero is involved in a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, we will continue to ensure the confidentiality of any Personal Data and give affected users notice before Personal Data is transferred or becomes subject to a different privacy policy.
a. For more details on how Service Companies handle your Personal Data and a list of those Service Companies, please see our
Main Sphero Privacy Policy
.
4.
Rights and Choices.
You may exercise the below Rights and Choices by emailing Sphero’s Data Protection Officer at
dpo@sphero.com
with a copy to
support@sphero.com
. Our mailing address is:
Sphero, Inc.
Attn: Legal, Privacy Policy
7121 B Shelby Ave
Dock 85
Greenville, TX 75402
a.
Access.
You may receive a list of your Personal Data that we process to the extent required and permitted by law.
b.
Rectification.
You may correct any Personal Data that we hold about you to the extent required and permitted by law.
c.
Erasure and Objection to Processing.
To the extent required by applicable law, you may request that we delete your Personal Data from our systems. You can stop future collection of all Data by the Application by uninstalling it.
d.
Data Export.
To the extent required by applicable law, we will send you a copy of the Personal Data we hold from you in a common portable format of our choice.
e.
Direct Marketing.
Residents of California (and others as required by applicable law) may request a list of Personal Data we have disclosed about you to third parties for direct marketing purposes during the preceding calendar year. This request must be written, signed, and mailed to us, unless otherwise required by applicable law. You may cease direct marketing from us in relation to the Application by emailing
support@sphero.com
, or by clicking the unsubscribe link in any promotional email we send you.
f.
Regulator Contact.
You have the right to contact or file a complaint with regulators or supervisory authorities about our processing of Personal Data. To do so, please contact your local data protection or consumer protection authority.
5.
Changes to This Privacy Policy.
This Privacy Policy is subject to occasional revision. If we make any changes to this Policy, we will change the "Last Updated" date above.
