Force Band™ By Sphero Privacy Policy
Last Updated: May 23, 2018
Sphero, Inc. (“
Sphero
”, "
we
" or “
us
”) is committed to protecting your and, where applicable, your child’s privacy.
This
Privacy Policy
describes how you and, where applicable, your child’s information is collected, used, and disclosed by Sphero from the mobile application entitled Force Band™ by Sphero (the “
Application
”), for the Force Band™ by Sphero device (the “
Toy
” or “
Force Band
”), and the services we offer through our Application and Toy (the Toy and Application together known as the “
Services
”). This Policy does not apply to websites, applications, or services that display or link to different privacy policies. Any third parties described below that process your data may not adhere to this Privacy Policy; Sphero expressly disclaims any and all liability for unauthorized processing by such third parties. For subjects not covered in this Policy, the
Main Sphero Privacy Policy
controls
.
Data We Collect.
We collect personal information from users of the Services, as described below.
a) Data You Provide to Us Upon Toy Configuration
.
Identity Data
: Your age
Contact Data
: If you are over 13 (or such age as local law dictates), you may choose to provide your email address.
b) Information Collected Automatically via Technology on our Services
Mobile Data
.
If you download our Application, we may collect the type of mobile device, device carrier, its software version, and the like.
Toy Data
:
Using Bluetooth, the Toy transmits Toy Data to the Application such as Toy identifier, when a Toy connects to an Application, when you click the “buy” button in the Application, date/time stamps, non-personal diagnostic data regarding how you use the Application, MAC Address or device identifier depending on the Toy, accelerometer data, crashes, and the like. If you choose to send us diagnostics, we may process your email address and Toy Data.
Use of Your Data.
Subject to your Rights and Choices below, we use your Data as follows.
We use information you submit to us as described in this Policy, as disclosed to you in our Services or in connection with our Services, including in the following ways:
a) Identity Data.
We use your Identity Data to comply with applicable privacy law. Specifically, we use your Identity Data to tell whether you are a child, as defined by local law. We may vary the parts of the Service available to you or the data collected about you based on your age to comply with applicable laws. For example, if according to your Identity Data, you are a “child” under applicable law, we do not collect Contact Data in the Application.
b) Contact Data.
We use your Contact Data to provide support services if you contact us, and for promotional marketing if you have
agreed
to receive such emails.
For example:
If you contact us through customer service or support, we will use your Contact Data to respond to your comments and questions, and to provide customer service.
For non-child users, if you have chosen to provide your Contact Data within the Application, we may send you newsletters, surveys, offers, and other promotional materials related to our Services, and for other direct marketing purposes. We may share your Contact Data with a Service Company (defined below) for this purpose. We do this to promote our products and issue our direct marketing.
c) Mobile Data and Toy Data.
We use the Toy Data and Mobile Data for our legitimate business interests, including:
to understand a user’s engagement in an activity or feature, for example which activities on the Toy the user played, time spent on activities, and data about any crashes during use;
to operate our Application and Services, internal operations, and systems, along with the Service Companies;
to improve the quality of experience when you interact with our Application and Services;
to provide, support, and maintain the Toy, Application, and features that enable people, including children, to enjoy the Toy and Application;
to ensure compliance with our
Terms of Use
; and
to secure our platform and network, investigate suspicious activity or violations of our terms or policies, and to protect the safety of Personal Data, including to prevent exploitation or other harms to which users may be particularly vulnerable.
d) Support.
If you contact us for support through the Application, we may collect first and last name, email address, and any information you choose to include in your query.
Service Companies.
We use third-party
Service Companies
to help provide and host the Application and the Service, to help with direct marketing, to help us automatically collect the Mobile and Toy data, to analyze the Toy Data, and to further our other legitimate business interests. We provide Personal Data to our Service Companies or other trusted businesses or persons to process it for us, based on our instructions and in compliance with this Privacy Policy and any other appropriate confidentiality and security measures. If Sphero is involved in a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, we will continue to ensure the confidentiality of any Personal Data and give affected users notice before Personal Data is transferred or becomes subject to a different privacy policy.
Direct Marketing.
We use Sailthru as an email list administrator. We share your Contact Data with them if you provide it to us.
For more details on how Service Companies handle your Personal Data, please see our
Main Sphero Privacy Policy
.
Rights and Choices.
You may exercise the below
Rights and Choices by emailing Sphero’s Data Protection Officer at
dpo@sphero.com
with a copy to
support@sphero.com
. Our mailing address is:
Sphero, Inc.
Attn: DPO
7121 B Shelby Ave
Dock 85
Greenville, TX 75402
a) Access.
You may receive a list of your Personal Data that we process to the extent required and permitted by law.
b) Rectification.
You may correct any Personal Data that we hold about you to the extent required and permitted by law.
c) Erasure and Objection to Processing.
To the extent required by applicable law, you may request that we delete your Personal Data from our systems. You can stop future collection of all Data by the Application by uninstalling it.
d) Data Export.
To the extent required by applicable law, we will send you a copy of the Personal Data we hold from you in a common portable format of our choice.
e) Direct Marketing.
Residents of California (and others as required by applicable law) may request a list of Personal Data we have disclosed about you to third parties for direct marketing purposes during the preceding calendar year. This request must be written, signed, and mailed to us, unless otherwise required by applicable law.
You may cease direct marketing from us in relation to the Application by emailing
support@sphero.com
, or by clicking the unsubscribe link in any promotional email we send you.
f) Regulator Contract.
You have the right to contact or file a complaint with regulators or supervisory authorities about our processing of Personal Data. To do so, please contact your local data protection or consumer protection authority.
Changes to This Privacy Policy.
This Privacy Policy is subject to occasional revision. If we make any changes to this Policy, we will change the "Last Updated" date above.
